Ingest CSV data to PostgreSQL database (DEPRECATED)

Source: R/ingest.R
ingest_csv_to_db.Rd

This function is deprecated. Please use ingest_to_working instead for ingesting data into the DuckLake database with automatic provenance tracking.

Loads transformed data into a PostgreSQL database with proper metadata.

Usage

ingest_csv_to_db(
  con,
  schema,
  transformed_data,
  d_flds_rd,
  d_gdir_data = NULL,
  workflow_info,
  overwrite = FALSE
)

Arguments

con

Database connection

schema

Database schema

transformed_data

Transformed data from transform_data()

d_flds_rd

Field redefinition data frame

d_gdir_data

Google Drive metadata (optional)

workflow_info

Workflow information (name, URL, etc.)

overwrite

Whether to overwrite existing tables

Value

Data frame with ingestion statistics

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
stats <- ingest_csv_to_db(
  con = db_connection,
  schema = "public",
  transformed_data = transformed_data,
  d_flds_rd = data_info$d_flds_rd,
  d_gdir_data = data_info$d_gdir_data,
  workflow_info = data_info$workflow_info
)
} # }
